		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>The drill sergeant gets in your face and snarls angrily.&nbsp;&nbsp;Let the lesson begin.<br><br>In PvP contests against necromancers you should win almost automatically against equal levels and at least 50/50 when they are 1 or 2 levels higher.  If you fail to achieve these rates of success, get schooled in the following.<br><br>Step 1 - Flash of Light (FoL).  Hands down this is the first step.  Stops most casters in their tracks unless they happen to have spells on their hotkeys.  If you fail to do this step immediately you can expect to lose 80 to 90 percent of the time.  Period.<br><br>Step 2 - Spook the Dead.  Get that pet outa there.  You don't need the damage and that necro doesn't need a body guard while he blindly runs around avoiding your sword and shield.  This step alone will likely save half your health or more.<br><br>Step 3 - Root that smug idiot in place and renew your Flash of Light.  Root can sometimes take a bit of time to get off and doesn't always work. As an alternative, be sure you have a very damaging bow with lots of arrows.  The good thing about a bow is that you can run and shoot, unlike a spell which requires no movement whatsoever.  Just be sure you get back into FoL range before it runs out.<br><br>Step 4 - Hack and bash.  Put the evil fool to the sword and bash as often as needed.<br><br>Repeat all steps as often as needed.<br><br>You can expect that when the necro regains his sight he will be throwing dots and taps at a rapid pace.  If he hasn't been able to cast spells for a bit, he will be panicky and in no mood to go soft on you.  If it gets to be too much then understand this, Cure Disease will actually remove some necro dots.  Toss another FoL at him and then do a cure.<br><br>It goes without saying that you better have your LOH available before the battle begins.  If for no other reason than to tick him off that he has to go through his necro process all over again to beat you.<br><br>You don't have to win, but you better wipe that smug look off his face.<br><br><br>Lanceor <br>Paladin of Mithanial Marr <br>Acceptor of 23 truths <br>Xegony Server <br><br>Perception is reality, but truth is virtuous. <br>-Mithian proverb<br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=97129516610266&num=5&page=&post=1&mid=97129516610266><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mform><tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>5 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
